============================================================
DERIVE g_k FROM WEIGHT FORMULA
============================================================
E_{2k}/E_0 = sum over configs of r pairs from m=n-2 slots
         = sum over domino subsets S with |S|=2k of 2^c/(n)_L
where c=#components, L=|S|=2k
So factor out 1/(n)_{2k}: g_k(m)/(n)_{2k} * 2 = sum 2^c/(n)_{2k}
=> contribution = (sum 2^{c-1}) * 2/(n)_{2k}
=> g_k(m) = sum over configs of k pairs in m+2k-1 positions of 2^{c-1}

Wait, that's not right. Let me reconsider.

Actually: the sum over all k-pair domino configs in positions 0..n-2
of E[prod Z] = sum of 2^c/(n)_{|S|}.
But |S| is NOT always 2k! Overlapping pairs share positions.

